body:
@snapshotpl @Seldaek The limit has indeed been reduced: 

V1: https://www.hipchat.com/docs/api/method/rooms/message
V2: https://www.hipchat.com/docs/apiv2/method/send_message

@Seldaek , I came here for the same issue: the limit of 10k is there, but Monolog doesn't really respect that: `HipChatHandler::write()` method doesn't check for the limits and just writes the content. I just tried an exception-trace message weighing 15k+ bytes, and Monolog didn't return any errors. However, Hipchat returns the following result: 

`{"error":{"code":400,"type":"Bad Request","message":"Message must be 10000 characters or less."}}`

Could you please add actual length checks into `HipChatHandler::write()` ? Actual writing is performed here: https://github.com/Seldaek/monolog/blob/master/src/Monolog/Handler/SocketHandler.php#L298
